00:48.800 --> 00:52.300
- Ferdinand.
- Hey, Bobby man. Hey, not now.

00:52.300 --> 00:55.200
Not now? I welcome you home,
and you play cold. What's up with that?

00:55.200 --> 00:56.800
Oh, man. Please.

00:56.800 --> 00:58.900
Ferdinand, are you working here?

00:58.800 --> 01:01.600
- Hejust gets out of Attica.
- Comstock.

01:01.600 --> 01:04.300
You don't write.
You don't call.

01:04.300 --> 01:06.600
I come out on the street with my partner
here, and you setting up for business.

01:06.600 --> 01:08.800
Bobby, I didn't even
know you was downtown.

01:08.700 --> 01:11.800
- You checking out this Lexus, huh?
- What? What Lexus? Man, no.

01:11.800 --> 01:14.800
- Just checking the atmosphere.
- You looking to take off Colombians now?

01:14.700 --> 01:18.200
'Cause that's living pretty large.

01:18.200 --> 01:21.600
Damn it! Robert, man, you pop up
like this, you ruin everything.

01:21.500 --> 01:24.500
- Man, a couple more minutes out there, and I'm gone!
- You know how that goes.

01:24.400 --> 01:28.400
First, you pay, and then maybe
you get a chance to play. Come on.

01:29.200 --> 01:30.900
Damn it!

02:46.800 --> 02:49.300
Can I help you?

02:49.300 --> 02:52.300
Ray Kahlins. I'm with
the, uh, HI DA task force.

02:52.200 --> 02:54.200
Which is
Detective Sipowicz's desk?

02:54.100 --> 02:56.200
- Over there.
- Thank you.

02:56.200 --> 02:58.200
I'll file that information.

02:58.100 --> 03:02.200
- How's it going, huh?
- Good. Who you guys all with?

03:02.100 --> 03:06.400
Son, if I tell you that, I gotta kill you. Hmm?

03:11.800 --> 03:14.400
- Yeah?
- Sergeant Ray Kahlins, Lieutenant.

03:14.300 --> 03:17.000
NYPD detail to
the HIDA task force.

03:17.000 --> 03:18.800
I got the memo you'd
be here on the Barnes case.

03:18.900 --> 03:23.300
Two drug crews shoot it out. Only casualty's
a 10-year-old on her way to school, huh?

03:23.200 --> 03:27.400
Yeah. We got two empty rooms you can use
in Anticrime. That's up on the third floor.

03:27.300 --> 03:32.300
- Great.
- I know I owe you a detective. You need any logistical help?

03:32.100 --> 03:34.500
You gotta be kidding.
We're federally funded, Lieutenant.

03:34.400 --> 03:37.300
We got new cars. We got
new radios. Unlimited overtime.

03:37.200 --> 03:39.500
Yeah. State police are
working with you too?

03:39.400 --> 03:43.200
Everyone but the cavalry.
We can't spend it fast enough.

03:43.100 --> 03:44.900
So how you doing
on the case?

03:44.900 --> 03:48.200
W- We're looking at some people.
We're working back on the crews.

03:48.100 --> 03:50.500
- Thanks for the space.
- Yeah.

03:52.300 --> 03:55.100
Hey, Diane?

03:56.300 --> 03:59.200
- Morning, boss.
- Yeah, morning. Um...

03:59.200 --> 04:01.300
We got a High-Intensity Drug Area
unit working out of the squad.

04:01.300 --> 04:05.000
- They're on the Barnes homicide?
- Yeah. It's a different kind of investigative work.

04:05.000 --> 04:08.300
Um, they've got federal money.
They can go a lot farther into a case.

04:08.200 --> 04:11.300
- It might be good experience for you working with them.
- Sure. I'd like that.

04:11.200 --> 04:15.600
The guy running the detail's from our job.
Sergeant Kahlins. Go out and introduce yourself.

04:15.500 --> 04:18.300
- I appreciate the look, Lieutenant.
- Yeah.

04:20.800 --> 04:23.100
Uh-huh.

04:23.100 --> 04:26.000
Excuse me. Young lady, you know
how to spell fornicate"?

04:27.100 --> 04:30.400
Never mind.
I'll just shorten it.

04:32.100 --> 04:35.900
Tread lightly through your thinking for me,
turning this Ferdinand loose.

04:35.800 --> 04:38.200
Andy, we bring him in, I gotta toss him.
I know I'm gonna find a gun.

04:38.100 --> 04:41.000
Perish the thought you take
a weapon off a stickup guy.

04:41.000 --> 04:44.900
He comes in on his own. He's off this piece.
He's not looking at a collar.

04:44.800 --> 04:47.700
- He's gonna have a whole lot better attitude.
- You see those tracks?

04:47.700 --> 04:51.000
- Yeah. He's been shooting up his whole life, coke and dope, both.
- So we know he's reliable.

04:51.000 --> 04:54.000
He'll show, Andy.
He'll make cases for us.

04:53.900 --> 04:56.100
I'll put the bag in the freshwater tank
till I go home.

04:56.100 --> 04:59.900
This little guy inflates himself,
those goldfish'll have a stroke.

04:59.700 --> 05:02.000
- Yeah, huh?
- Yeah.

05:02.000 --> 05:04.600
Oh, man.

05:04.600 --> 05:06.800
- Who's that?
- Some loudmouth crap-artist.

05:06.900 --> 05:10.500
Hey, Andy. I was just writing you
an obscene note.

05:10.500 --> 05:12.700
How's it going there, Kahlins?
This is Bobby Simone.

05:12.700 --> 05:15.900
- Sergeant Ray Kahlins.
- Good to meet you, Sarge. Diane Russell.

05:15.800 --> 05:18.400
- Hi.
- Hi. How's it going, Diane?

05:18.400 --> 05:20.800
I just got some good news. My boss
wants me to work on your task force.

05:20.700 --> 05:23.000
I knew I liked that guy.

05:23.000 --> 05:26.400
So, Andy,
still closing down the bars?

05:27.600 --> 05:29.600
No. Not too much.

05:29.600 --> 05:32.100
I've only met a few people in my life
could drink me under a table.

05:32.100 --> 05:34.500
And this guy is one of them.

05:37.200 --> 05:40.500
- So this is where you landed, huh?
- Yeah.

05:40.500 --> 05:42.700
- It's not bad. It's not bad for precinct work.
- Andy.

05:44.500 --> 05:48.400
Yeah. Look, I'd stick around for more career
evaluation, but we gotta talk to this guy.

05:48.300 --> 05:50.200
- Go on. Get out of here.
- Nice to meet you.

05:50.300 --> 05:52.600
- Same here.
- Come on. Let's take the long way to the coffee room.

05:52.600 --> 05:56.600
Hey, Diane, body in a basement on Hester
Street. You want to work it with us?

05:56.400 --> 05:58.600
Boss just assigned me to the task force
on the Barnes homicide.

05:58.500 --> 06:00.300
Hey, good for you. That's great.

06:00.300 --> 06:02.800
Yeah. James Martinez, Greg Medavoy,
Sergeant Ray Kahlins.

06:02.800 --> 06:05.600
- How's it going?
- I noticed you got a Ranger jacket on there.

06:05.600 --> 06:08.600
Our Miss Abandando,
big Ranger fan.

06:08.600 --> 06:10.500
Is that so? I won this on a bet.

06:10.500 --> 06:12.800
So you got a stinker
down on Hester Street?

06:12.800 --> 06:15.100
Yeah, yeah. We don't know
how long it's been there.

06:15.000 --> 06:18.300
Yeah. You know, I used to own a couple
of them loft buildings over there by Ludlow.

06:18.300 --> 06:22.000
Zoning regs wouldn't let me
develop them the way I wanted to.

06:22.000 --> 06:25.000
So I said, 'The hell with this. "I sold
the two of them off, cleared myself 80 large.

06:24.800 --> 06:26.300
- Is that right?
- Yeah.

06:26.400 --> 06:28.500
Anyways, we better
get over there.

06:28.500 --> 06:33.600
Diane, think you could point me in the general
direction of the, uh, Anti-Crime section?

06:33.400 --> 06:37.200
- It's right upstairs.
- Okay. Guys, let's go. We're moving out.

06:37.100 --> 06:39.900
- When'd you own those lofts?
- Well, I sold them about five years ago.

06:39.900 --> 06:44.100
Made myself somewheres
between $80,000, $90,000.

06:54.500 --> 06:56.700
Watching you drink coffee
makes my teeth hurt.

06:56.700 --> 06:59.400
I'm a fiend for sweets.

06:59.300 --> 07:01.400
Dope, cocaine, sweets.

07:02.600 --> 07:05.700
All I want is everything.

07:05.700 --> 07:08.800
Say, Ferdinand, whatever happened to
that tall guy you used to hunt with?

07:08.700 --> 07:11.200
Antoine? He dead.

07:11.100 --> 07:13.700
Got the virus.
Went real quick.

07:13.700 --> 07:16.000
A lot of guys
have got that bug now, man.

07:16.000 --> 07:19.400
Yeah. A lot of guys do.

07:22.700 --> 07:24.600
So what do you got
for show and tell?

07:24.500 --> 07:27.700
- Rent's due, huh?
- First of the month, holmes.

07:29.900 --> 07:32.000
How about I put two bodies
on Marcus Edmonds?

07:32.000 --> 07:34.100
I mean he dead now.
So he's past minding.

07:34.000 --> 07:37.700
You're gonna give us paper clearances
off Marcus Edmonds?

07:37.700 --> 07:41.800
Guy's been dead for four months. Every snitch
in the city's still trying to put murders on him.

07:41.700 --> 07:44.900
Marcus like to shot about 20 people
'fore he caught a bullet his own self.

07:44.900 --> 07:48.800
I'm gonna tell you about
that double, LaGuardia Homes.

07:50.100 --> 07:52.400
Them bodies in the stairwell.

07:52.400 --> 07:56.500
- Edmonds did those shootings?
- Sure did. I got names, numbers.

07:56.300 --> 08:00.700
I know who was with him. I know
the whole story behind that foolishness.

08:00.600 --> 08:03.400
All right. All right.
We'll get back to that.

08:04.300 --> 08:06.200
How about something fresh?

08:08.200 --> 08:10.900
How about that bodega last month, Avenue B,"
where the counter man got shot?

08:10.800 --> 08:13.400
- How about it?
- Fresh enough?

08:13.400 --> 08:16.800
- Let's hear it.
- Shooter was Lynwood Truett.

08:16.700 --> 08:18.700
Used to be with
the Diamond in the Raw Crew.

08:18.600 --> 08:20.600
They cut him loose when
he kept messing up the count.

08:20.600 --> 08:23.400
Second man in that job
was Andre Boyd.

08:23.400 --> 08:26.500
He been on Rikers last couple of weeks.
You need a witness? You got Marletta Weeks.

08:26.500 --> 08:28.900
She Boyd's girlfriend.
She drove 'em there.

08:28.800 --> 08:32.200
- Where's this Marletta live?
- Alphabet City somewheres.

08:32.000 --> 08:35.000
You'll find her through Social Services.
She get a check.

08:36.200 --> 08:39.700
Can I get back
to my own little drama now?

08:39.500 --> 08:41.799
Who were those Colombians
you were looking to take off?

08:44.100 --> 08:46.900
- Man, they're my business.
- Your business?

08:46.900 --> 08:49.800
Damn straight. You got your own business.
I'm helping you with that.

08:49.800 --> 08:51.700
But I got my own thing,
and you messing with it.

08:51.700 --> 08:53.600
I tend to mess
with armed robbery. Yeah.

08:53.700 --> 08:55.600
Bobby, man,
chill your partner down.

08:55.600 --> 08:57.600
No. I got a vision of
a street full of taxpayers...

08:57.600 --> 09:00.300
getting caught in
the cross fire, Ferdinand...

09:00.300 --> 09:02.200
while you do business
with your.38.

09:02.200 --> 09:04.600
.44.

09:04.600 --> 09:07.400
My mistake.

09:07.400 --> 09:09.900
Niggers see that big gun come out,
they don't argue.

09:09.900 --> 09:12.700
They looking down that big-ass barrel
like it's the Lincoln Tunnel...

09:12.700 --> 09:14.600
and theyJersey bound.

09:14.600 --> 09:18.400
Man, they give it up.
Wail like bitches.

09:18.300 --> 09:21.200
Only fools stop
and trifle with a.44.

09:23.000 --> 09:25.000
I need your beeper number,
Ferdinand.

09:25.900 --> 09:27.800
Yeah, okay.

09:27.900 --> 09:30.500
Then you can take off
while we check out your stuff.

09:30.300 --> 09:32.400
Can't even
write my numbers good.

09:32.500 --> 09:34.800
I should've stayed in school.

09:56.300 --> 09:59.200
This guy's stabbed up pretty good.
But there's no decomp.

09:59.100 --> 10:01.900
- Actually, he looks pretty fresh.
- Yeah.

10:01.900 --> 10:04.600
It's the rest of the room
that stinks like death.

10:04.500 --> 10:08.200
Santeria-
offering to the saints.

10:08.100 --> 10:11.100
- Huh?
- Our guy's a santero, a priest.

10:11.000 --> 10:13.300
See?
He's wearing all white.

10:13.200 --> 10:15.500
They do that for the first two years
for purity.

10:16.800 --> 10:19.200
This is where
he must've made his offerings.

10:19.200 --> 10:22.200
No pockets on this outfit.
I don't see no I.D.

10:22.200 --> 10:25.500
Look at this.
Goats, roosters...

10:25.500 --> 10:29.200
The santero sacrifices to
the ancient gods and Catholic saints.

10:29.100 --> 10:33.800
He uses them for white magic. No black
magic though. That's Palo Mayombe.

10:33.800 --> 10:35.700
You know all about this stuff.

10:35.700 --> 10:38.400
Yeah. Tio Pepe, my uncle,
was a santero.

10:38.400 --> 10:42.700
On Sundays, you couldn't go into my cousin's
basement without stepping on a rooster's head.

10:42.600 --> 10:47.200
People from the neighborhood would come to
my Tio Pepe to put a trabajito on their enemies.

10:47.100 --> 10:49.800
- What's a trabajito?
- That's like a little work, like a hex.

10:49.700 --> 10:52.600
Well, h-how are
we gonna I.D. This guy?

10:52.600 --> 10:55.500
I'll call Father Ramos
over at Saint Luis's.

10:55.500 --> 10:59.800
- You'd call a Catholic priest ab-about a
witch doctor? - They're not witch doctors, Greg.

10:59.700 --> 11:03.000
Spanish neighborhoods, Catholic priests
tend to deal with these guys a little.

11:03.000 --> 11:05.200
Yeah? Live and learn.

11:05.100 --> 11:07.900
Life's not all
Ozzie and Harriet.

11:07.900 --> 11:13.500
Yeah. This is definitely not
the Nelson family rec room.

11:16.000 --> 11:19.700
Morrisey and Regina caught that bodega
homicide your C.I. Told you about.

11:19.600 --> 11:22.300
They're coming in on a 41.

11:22.300 --> 11:25.300
We can check out this woman, Marletta,
who supposedly drove the getaway car.

11:25.200 --> 11:27.500
Turn her over
to Morrisey when he gets in.

11:27.500 --> 11:30.300
Information the C.I. Gave up on those
LaGuardia Homes homicides checks out.

11:30.300 --> 11:32.200
Putting those on Marcus Edmonds.

11:32.300 --> 11:34.300
Guy's information is straight,
Lieu. It always has been.

11:34.300 --> 11:36.600
- So, you gonna need anything
from the snitch fund? - No. Uh-uh.

11:36.600 --> 11:38.700
Is he up on a charge?

11:38.700 --> 11:41.700
- He just got out. Did a three-year bit.
- So what do you got over him?

11:41.700 --> 11:44.900
He's probably doing some things that
we don't want to know about.

11:44.800 --> 11:46.700
Give me a hint.

11:48.300 --> 11:50.200
The bit was just
sticking up drug dealers.

11:50.200 --> 11:53.100
He's been doing his act longer
than I've been on thejob, Lieu.

11:53.100 --> 11:55.500
And I have never once heard
of a civilian getting hurt.

11:55.400 --> 11:57.900
I don't want this guy thinking
he's got a free ride in my precinct.

11:57.900 --> 12:00.800
- He knows it's not like that.
- Mm-hmm.

12:00.800 --> 12:04.600
- Meanwhile we get these clearances.
- Clearances are great.

12:10.500 --> 12:13.500
You figure this Ferdinand
for having a virus like his tall friend, Antoine?

12:13.400 --> 12:16.700
- Yeah. That's how I read it.
- When you saw this guy was looking...

12:16.600 --> 12:19.300
to take off a Colombian,
you said he was stepping up.

12:19.300 --> 12:21.600
Mm-hmm.
He used to hit independents.

12:21.600 --> 12:26.000
A lot of people will figure taking off
a Cali bagman an assisted form of suicide.

12:26.000 --> 12:29.300
You thinking 'cause maybe he's got the virus,
he's, uh, taking more chances.

12:29.200 --> 12:32.300
He wants to risk getting his head
blown off, that's his problem.

12:32.300 --> 12:35.500
But he may not be as careful
with civilians as he used to be either.

12:35.400 --> 12:37.400
I don't figure him like that, Andy.

12:37.300 --> 12:40.000
- It may be worth a conversation.
- Detective squad. One moment.

12:41.000 --> 12:43.400
Welfare's on line two
about a Marletta Weeks.

12:43.400 --> 12:46.100
Ah.

12:46.000 --> 12:48.000
- Hey.
- How's it going?

12:48.100 --> 12:51.600
Good. So you're detailed
to that HI DA unit, huh?

12:51.400 --> 12:54.100
- Yeah.
- Gonna get you some profile.

12:59.800 --> 13:02.900
That Marletta picks up her welfare check
at a post office box.

13:02.800 --> 13:04.800
We'll get the address
from the postal inspector.

13:04.900 --> 13:08.100
Yeah. You got detail on
that Barnes investigation, huh?

13:08.000 --> 13:09.600
You work with my boss before?

13:09.700 --> 13:12.800
Kahlins, yeah. Don't forget
your hip boots tomorrow.

13:13.900 --> 13:17.300
- Sylvia.
- Hi.

13:17.200 --> 13:21.100
Some affidavit information
for some warrants from a Sergeant Kahlins?

13:21.000 --> 13:24.400
- Um. He's upstairs.
- Okay.

13:24.400 --> 13:28.100
- He can come down here. You don't have to go climbing up.
- I'll go get him.

13:28.000 --> 13:31.900
- What you getting warrants for?
- We're going out on a couple houses tomorrow.

13:31.900 --> 13:34.800
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

13:36.200 --> 13:37.900
Excuse me.

13:45.900 --> 13:47.800
Has to go to the bathroom
all the time now.

13:47.800 --> 13:51.500
I didn't figure that task force
would be going through any doors.

13:54.000 --> 13:56.600
- Excuse me. Um-
- May I help you?

13:56.500 --> 13:59.000
- Father Ramos.
- Yes?

13:58.900 --> 14:00.900
I'm Detective Martinez.
Thanks for coming in.

14:01.000 --> 14:05.400
You spoke on the phone about a santero
found murdered on Hester Street.

14:05.300 --> 14:07.900
- This is Detective Medavoy.
- Hi.

14:07.900 --> 14:09.900
Yeah.

14:09.900 --> 14:12.700
This is from
the medical examiner's office.

14:12.600 --> 14:15.800
So, I'm sure he, uh-
I'm sure he's looked better to you.

14:18.100 --> 14:20.000
It's Miguel. Miguel Marquez.

14:20.000 --> 14:22.900
- Do you know who stabbed him?
- Well, we're looking into it now.

14:22.900 --> 14:25.900
Father, as a santero, uh,
was this man well regarded?

14:25.800 --> 14:29.300
Well, I can't recall anything ill
being said about Mr. Marquez.

14:29.300 --> 14:31.400
He practiced
the white magic only.

14:31.400 --> 14:33.900
Naturally, we discourage
the practice completely.

14:33.900 --> 14:37.800
Would you know of an address
for Mr. Marquez? Uh, next of kin?

14:37.800 --> 14:40.500
Yes. It should be in our church records.
M- May I use your phone?

14:40.400 --> 14:43.600
Just dial nine, Father.

14:47.200 --> 14:51.100
So, Detective Russell tells me, uh,
that you're Andy Sipowicz's better half.

14:51.000 --> 14:53.100
That's right.

14:53.000 --> 14:57.100
- Andy and me have gone through some doors in this job.
- Is that so?

14:57.100 --> 15:00.800
- We were in service together at the same time too.
- Vietnam?

15:00.700 --> 15:03.300
Yes, ma'am.
During the worst of it.

15:04.300 --> 15:06.600
All right.
Basis for application?

15:06.500 --> 15:10.200
Confidential information and
proceeds of surveillance.

15:10.100 --> 15:12.500
State criminal enterprise
you believe is being conducted.

15:12.500 --> 15:14.900
Sale and
warehouse of drugs.

15:14.900 --> 15:17.400
We are gonna get
a title three out of this.

15:17.400 --> 15:20.100
- That is six months, minimum.
- Title three's a wiretap?

15:20.100 --> 15:24.800
You get a wire up,
and the overtime really starts to flow.

15:24.600 --> 15:28.200
If you think that these warrants aren't
going to be productive, Sergeant...

15:28.200 --> 15:31.000
I have much better things
to do with my time.

15:31.000 --> 15:34.800
Well, no, no. The warrants
are definitely gonna be productive.

15:34.600 --> 15:36.600
So, I'm just looking ahead.

15:36.600 --> 15:40.500
I'm, uh, letting Detective Russell here
know what the next step would be.

15:40.500 --> 15:42.300
I'm reeducating her
from precinct work.

15:42.300 --> 15:47.200
See, now, federal time,
everything stretches out.

15:47.000 --> 15:49.000
They say it's like that
in Hawaii.

16:00.800 --> 16:02.900
Yes, this is my son.

16:02.900 --> 16:05.500
I'm very sorry for your loss.

16:05.500 --> 16:08.300
Did your son recently have
an argument with anyone, Mrs. Marquez?

16:08.300 --> 16:11.100
- Have anyone angry with him?
- No one was angry with my son.

16:10.900 --> 16:15.300
Unless... those who deal
with dark magic.

16:15.300 --> 16:17.300
Those who call the saints for evil.

16:17.200 --> 16:19.300
Paio Mayombay," huh?

16:19.300 --> 16:21.700
What do you know
about Palo Mayombe?

16:21.700 --> 16:24.100
No. L-I-I just heard the term.

16:24.000 --> 16:27.000
Can we take a look around
at some of Miguel's things?

16:27.000 --> 16:29.500
Ta bien.

16:43.300 --> 16:45.200
Ew.

