22:27.300 --> 22:31.100
- What's his name?
- Goose Tatum.

22:32.700 --> 22:35.300
Can't blame a guy for trying.

22:39.500 --> 22:43.000
Robert, you starting to
remind me of my cousin, Darnell.

22:43.000 --> 22:45.200
Oh, yeah? How's that?

22:45.100 --> 22:47.100
Darnell, he a country boy.

22:47.000 --> 22:49.400
He used to come from Carolina,
spend the summer in the big city.

22:49.300 --> 22:51.600
At first it was good
to see him, you know?

22:51.500 --> 22:54.100
ByJuly, he got to acting
all crazy, jumping bad.

22:54.100 --> 22:56.700
It be like, Yo, coz.
You done wore the welcome out."

23:01.600 --> 23:03.500
I gotta ask you something,
Ferdinand.

23:05.100 --> 23:07.200
You got that virus?

23:08.200 --> 23:12.600
- Got caught up in that, yeah.
- Sorry.

23:12.600 --> 23:16.100
I guess it ain't like I don't deserve it.
All these years of running and gunning.

23:16.000 --> 23:18.100
I finally got tested up at Comstock.

23:18.000 --> 23:20.700
Felt like I knew the answer
before they told me.

23:20.700 --> 23:23.800
This takeoff with the Colombians
that you're working on...

23:23.700 --> 23:26.100
you running
a little wild with that?

23:26.000 --> 23:27.900
- What you mean?
- You know what I mean.

23:27.900 --> 23:30.200
Are you getting reckless?

23:30.100 --> 23:33.900
You think I'm looking
to go out in a blaze of glory?

23:33.900 --> 23:36.800
No, man. I don't want
to get thin and all.

23:36.800 --> 23:39.100
But that happens, I carry it.

23:39.100 --> 23:42.900
- You a soldier, huh?
- I'm a Viking, holmes.

23:45.600 --> 23:48.500
You know about this drug crew
that stashes over on Rivington?

23:48.500 --> 23:52.400
Main name I got is
some gangster named Freeland.

23:54.600 --> 23:56.600
This more rent?

23:56.500 --> 23:58.700
Favor.

24:03.300 --> 24:08.500
Marvin Freeland.
He's only half gangster.

24:08.400 --> 24:11.900
The other half all punk.
I hit his stash twice this year.

24:11.800 --> 24:13.800
We think Freeland's crew
is part of the cross fire...

24:13.900 --> 24:16.800
that killed this 10-year-old girl
on Canal Street last month.

24:16.600 --> 24:19.700
Yeah. I seen it on the news.

24:19.700 --> 24:24.000
Back in the day, a player walk up,
put the gun to the back of the guy's head.

24:23.900 --> 24:26.400
Make sure he hit the right nigger.

24:26.300 --> 24:30.700
Now you got fools, 15 to a clip, semi-autos,
spraying a whole damn street.

24:30.700 --> 24:34.900
- You think you might talk to someone about this Freeland?
- Someone?

24:34.700 --> 24:36.700
Another cop.
Just give him some background.

24:36.600 --> 24:38.400
Robert, don't make me out a bitch.

24:38.500 --> 24:41.900
Ferdinand, I would relay it,
but you're not registered as a C.I.

24:41.700 --> 24:44.400
And this guy, he looks
for reasons not to do his job.

24:44.400 --> 24:46.700
Dead girl his case?

24:48.300 --> 24:50.300
Yeah, okay.

24:51.800 --> 24:53.900
Appreciate it, Ferdinand.

24:53.800 --> 24:55.800
Fish guy gonna come?

24:55.700 --> 24:59.200
- You all right with that?
- Yeah.

25:04.400 --> 25:06.900
Hey, Robert, do I look
like that Unabomber?

25:11.300 --> 25:13.800
I'm, uh, Parole Officer
Rudy Haysbert.

25:13.700 --> 25:17.000
Oh, I'm Greg Medavoy.
Come on in.

25:16.900 --> 25:19.300
- Appreciate you coming down.
- I assume one of my cases went south?

25:19.300 --> 25:22.400
- Andy.
- We'll talk over here.

25:22.400 --> 25:25.200
- Oh, uh, my partner, James Martinez.
- How's it going?

25:25.100 --> 25:26.600
This is
Parole Officer Haysbert.

25:26.600 --> 25:29.500
If you'd told me which one of
my parolees you were interested in...

25:29.500 --> 25:31.500
we could've done
this whole thing on the phone.

25:31.500 --> 25:37.400
