Been stalling a half hour.

28:49.800 --> 28:52.800
- Is that the original door?
- Yeah.

28:55.500 --> 28:57.800
- Get this off of here.
- What's going on?

28:57.800 --> 29:00.200
Shut up.

29:14.200 --> 29:16.400
Ho.

29:16.400 --> 29:18.700
Know anything
about this, Larry?

29:18.700 --> 29:21.100
- Mm-mmm.
- Mm-mmm.

29:21.100 --> 29:23.500
Let's take a ride anyway.

29:24.400 --> 29:28.900
Come on.
Let me see those hands again.

29:40.700 --> 29:43.300
I recognize this one.
His name is Gabriel Mota.

29:44.500 --> 29:47.600
He came last month to my son,
Miguel, for un trabajo.

29:47.500 --> 29:50.400
And what did they want
the trabajo to do for him?

29:50.400 --> 29:53.400
- To make him invisible.
- Invisible?

29:53.300 --> 29:57.000
- Si. He wanted not to be seen.
- For what reason?

29:56.900 --> 30:00.200
For the police not
to be able to see him.

30:00.200 --> 30:04.200
And, uh, your son made
un trabayo" for Gabriel Mota.

30:04.100 --> 30:06.800
Yes. He made this man
invisible. Si.

30:06.700 --> 30:12.300
Then he came back very angry because
the police had stopped him in his car...

30:12.200 --> 30:14.500
because his license plates were...

30:14.400 --> 30:17.100
How do you say?
Were exploded."

30:17.000 --> 30:21.400
- They expired?
- Yes. He said, 'How can the police see him?"

30:21.300 --> 30:26.500
- And what did your son say?
- Well, he explained that un trabajo doesn't last forever.

30:26.400 --> 30:29.100
You have to keep coming back.

30:29.100 --> 30:30.800
And how did this man
take the explanation?

30:30.800 --> 30:33.600
He doesn't stop being angry.

30:33.600 --> 30:36.100
So my son said, Then go find
yourself somebody else."

30:36.000 --> 30:39.900
Mrs. Marquez, uh, the way
you looked at these photographs...

30:39.800 --> 30:41.700
could you do the same
with a group of men?

30:41.800 --> 30:45.600
- Try to I.D. This Gabriel Mota?
- Yes, all right.

30:45.500 --> 30:48.700
- See, we'll bring him into the station house.
- Mm-hmm.

30:48.700 --> 30:51.900
Assuming he's visible to the officers
that go looking for him.

30:53.200 --> 30:56.600
This man's federal, Larry.
I'm NYPD.

30:56.600 --> 31:00.200
Reason I'm talking to you is 'cause even
with all that weight we found in your door...

31:00.100 --> 31:02.100
you could still keep this
in state court.

31:02.100 --> 31:05.400
- That means no mandatory minimums.
- State court's Rockefeller Law.

31:05.400 --> 31:10.200
Last month a 10-year-old girl named Janelle
Barnes got caught in a cross fire on Canal Street.

31:10.100 --> 31:13.400
Give up the right answers
in her homicide...

31:13.400 --> 31:15.400
maybe it's not clear the stash
was in your possession.

31:15.400 --> 31:18.600
Then Rockefeller
wouldn't apply.

31:18.500 --> 31:20.500
I need to hear a D.A. Say it.

31:20.400 --> 31:22.400
You got the right answers
on the Barnes homicide?

31:22.300 --> 31:24.600
Yeah. I could give you those.

31:26.200 --> 31:28.700
I'll get a D.A.

31:28.700 --> 31:31.700
If somebody robs you
a few times, Larry...

31:31.600 --> 31:35.900
you might want to figure
a new place to keep your drugs.

31:35.900 --> 31:38.800
Scumbag!

31:44.600 --> 31:47.600
- Why did you do that, Kahlins?
- I'll find the D.A.

31:47.600 --> 31:49.800
