Martinez and Medavoy are in the squad.

32:01.000 --> 32:02.900
- Thanks.
- I'll get 'em.

32:02.900 --> 32:05.400
Oh, don't let me hit this guy.

32:05.400 --> 32:10.900
You told this Black Larry it was off him getting
robbed we knew where to look for his stash.

32:10.800 --> 32:13.500
She's downstairs taking a statement.
She'll be up in about 20 minutes.

32:13.500 --> 32:18.100
So Simone's guy does us a favor.
Huh? He goes out of his way.

32:18.000 --> 32:23.300
Now, the thanks he's gonna get the first time
this Larry gets a message to a visitor...

32:23.100 --> 32:26.000
Simone's guy
is gonna get whacked.

32:26.000 --> 32:28.900
You see my problem yet, Ray?
You understand what my problem is now?

32:28.800 --> 32:30.800
Boy, you guys
get thick with your C.I.'s.

32:30.800 --> 32:34.800
This is an unregistered informant.
A stickup man.

32:34.700 --> 32:36.900
He puts guns to people's heads.

32:36.900 --> 32:40.600
Excuse me, but I'm not worried whether
this guy makes it to his retirement party.

32:40.500 --> 32:43.100
Let me know
when the D.A. Gets here.

32:59.000 --> 33:01.900
You and your partner ought to hang around
in case this D.O.A.'s mother...

33:01.700 --> 33:03.500
don't pick this Gabriel Mota out.

33:03.600 --> 33:07.000
- No problem.
- Hey, uh, did this guy indicate...

33:06.900 --> 33:08.900
to you at all that
he thought he was invisible?

33:08.800 --> 33:10.900
- Invisible?
- Yeah.

33:11.000 --> 33:13.200
- No. Hejust kept asking were we real cops.
- Ah.

33:13.200 --> 33:15.500
You know why he was
asking that?

33:15.500 --> 33:17.900
The guy bought a spell
to make him invisible to the police.

33:17.900 --> 33:19.800
- No kidding?
- Yeah.

33:19.700 --> 33:22.300
Homicide we'd like the guy for,
the D.O.A.'s a Santeria priest.

33:22.200 --> 33:25.100
This Mota guy goes to him
to cast a spell on his parole officer...

33:25.000 --> 33:27.000
to make Mota invisible
to the cops.

33:27.000 --> 33:30.700
Yeah. So, when he don't get satisfaction,
he kills the Santeria priest...

33:30.700 --> 33:35.200
goes looking for another Santeria guy
to cast a better invisibility spell.

33:35.000 --> 33:38.600
- What room's the guy in?
- One of your detectives told my partner to put him in 3.

33:38.400 --> 33:42.400
I'm gonna move this Mota guy into the pokey
room before I bring down Mrs. Marquez.

33:42.400 --> 33:44.600
Yeah, good.

33:44.600 --> 33:47.100
So I guess the guy must figure
he got beat twice on his spells, huh?

33:47.100 --> 33:49.600
- Second priest didn't do any better for him than the D.O.A.
- Yeah.

33:49.600 --> 33:53.700
You see, James, uh, maybe that's
still open to debate. I got an idea.

33:57.900 --> 34:01.800
Hey, where'd this
Gabriel Mota guy go?

34:01.800 --> 34:05.000
Well, I thought you said
they had him in Interview 3.

34:04.900 --> 34:06.800
They said they left him in here.

34:06.900 --> 34:10.100
Those guys that brought him in here,
were they cops, or security guards?

34:10.000 --> 34:12.400
Security guards. For gosh sakes, Greg.
What difference does it make?

34:12.300 --> 34:16.000
Yeah, yeah. We got bigger
problems now.

34:17.100 --> 34:19.199
There's a suspect missing.

34:22.000 --> 34:25.500
Where could he have gone? You didn't
forget to lock the door, did you, Greg?

34:25.500 --> 34:29.900
Oh, yeah, yeah. Blame me.
Well, I guess we gotta tell the lieutenant.

34:29.800 --> 34:32.500
Man, this is one conversation
I'm not looking forward to.

34:32.400 --> 34:38.300
I mean, what are we gonna say to him?
You know, that the guy went invisible on us?

34:38.199 --> 34:40.600
I don't know.

34:42.699 --> 34:48.600
Hey, Gabriel, uh, when you go down
the hallway, don't forget to turn left.

34:48.500 --> 34:51.800
Yeah, and go in the door on the end there.
That's where we run our lineups.

34:51.699 --> 34:56.300
- You see me?
- Oh, just the last little while you started to materialize.

35:07.600 --> 35:11.200
So, no, uh, lesson tonight for AndyJ?

35:11.000 --> 35:14.200
He's got an orientation lecture
at his job.

35:14.200 --> 35:16.500
You gonna give
the heads-up to Ferdinand?

35:16.500 --> 35:20.100
I'm not putting this guy up for pope,
but there was nothing in this for him.

35:20.100 --> 35:22.000
Mm-hmm.
He was looking to help.

35:22.000 --> 35:23.900
That's all he was
looking to do, Ferdinand.

35:23.900 --> 35:25.800
And Kahlins winds up
jamming him up.

35:25.800 --> 35:28.000
The world's on its ass
when a stickup guy's more stand-up...

35:28.000 --> 35:30.300
than somebody
you're working with.

35:32.000 --> 35:35.100
- Oh, there they are.
- Hey.

35:35.100 --> 35:36.600
- Yeah.
- How are you doing?

35:36.600 --> 35:38.900
Good.

35:42.800 --> 35:46.100
- How'd you do?
- Uh, this Larry gave up the shooter.

35:46.100 --> 35:48.200
- From the other crew?
- Mm-hmm.

35:48.100 --> 35:50.800
- He said he was an eyewitness and agreed to testify.
- That's great.

35:50.800 --> 35:53.500
Downside, my boss
just walked in to celebrate.

35:53.500 --> 35:56.100
- Yes!
- Looks like he had a head start.

35:56.100 --> 35:59.300
Right-hand desk drawer,
that's where he keeps his bottle.

35:59.300 --> 36:03.400
- Always my personal favorite.
- I don't know how guys drink without a purse.

36:03.200 --> 36:05.000
Andy, were you and he
in uniform together?

36:05.000 --> 36:07.700
- You were in the bag with Kahlins?
- No.

36:07.600 --> 36:09.900
He said you went through
doors together...

36:09.900 --> 36:12.100
and you were
in service together in Vietnam.

36:12.100 --> 36:14.900
I knew you were
never detectives together.

36:14.800 --> 36:17.500
Excuse me.

36:19.400 --> 36:22.700
Hey, Ray.

36:22.700 --> 36:25.300
Hey, Andy! You ready to
fall off the wagon, huh?

36:25.300 --> 36:29.800
Ray, could I- Could I talk to you
for a minute privately over here?

36:29.700 --> 36:31.700
- What? Now?
- Yeah. Now. Just for a minute over here.

36:37.500 --> 36:41.600
- When were you in 'Nam?
- 1969.

36:41.400 --> 36:45.600
- Oh, yeah? What unit?
- Americal 198.

36:45.600 --> 36:48.300
Yeah? What base camp?

36:48.200 --> 36:50.000
Some gook village
outside of Saigon. What?

36:50.000 --> 36:53.200
- Do you remember all the names?
- Yeah. Every one of'em.

36:54.600 --> 36:56.500
Here's the deal, Ray.

36:56.500 --> 36:58.600
I don't know what the hell
you get out of it.

36:58.600 --> 37:03.500
But as far as I'm concerned, you can tell people
that you and me went through doors together.

37:03.400 --> 37:07.200
You can tell 'em you own the World Trade Center,
and you were married to Marilyn Monroe.

37:07.100 --> 37:12.200
You feel free to tell people that you put
every gangster since Legs Diamond behind bars...

37:12.100 --> 37:17.800
but Ray, you cannot lie
about what happened in Vietnam.

37:17.700 --> 37:22.000
Because that is an insult to people who
were there and who did what had to be done.

37:21.800 --> 37:24.600
I was in Vietnam, 1969.

37:24.600 --> 37:27.000
In what capacity, Ray?

37:27.000 --> 37:29.500
A maintenance unit.

37:31.100 --> 37:35.900
Then you say that. You tell the truth,
or you don't say anything at all.

37:35.800 --> 37:38.600
Do you hear me, Ray? Huh?
Or do we need to take this outside?

37:38.600 --> 37:40.600
See? That has always
been your problem, Sipowicz.

37:40.600 --> 37:43.800
That's why you're still doing precinct work.
You never learned to lighten up.

37:43.800 --> 37:47.600
You say anything you want, Ray,
but not about 'Nam. All right?

37:47.400 --> 37:49.400
Not about 'Nam.

37:50.900 --> 37:53.900
Andy. Andy,
wejust got beeped.

37:57.200 --> 37:59.200
Yeah.

38:03.100 --> 38:06.900
Fancy. He wants us to check out some
robbery/assault. Diane'll take Sylvia home.

38:06.800 --> 38:10.700
- What's going on?
- A couple of Colombians got taken off on Grand Street.

38:24.300 --> 38:26.200
- Hey.
- Hey.

38:28.000 --> 38:30.100
- Let me see your complainant report.
- They don't want to make one.

38:30.000 --> 38:33.400
Get this. They say
they don't know each other.

38:33.300 --> 38:37.100
This one says he fell. The other one
said he got hit, but he's not sure by whom.

38:37.000 --> 38:39.000
They don't want the police.

38:43.200 --> 38:45.100
Mm-hmm.
So you fell down?

38:45.200 --> 38:48.300
- Si.
- By accident?

38:49.300 --> 38:52.600
- Accidental. Si.
- And you weren't robbed.

38:52.600 --> 38:55.500
- No robbery.
- And you're not a drug dealer.

38:55.400 --> 38:59.000
And a black guy with a scar right here
and track marks on both his hands...

38:59.000 --> 39:03.600
he didn't jump you and stick a gun
the size of a drainage pipe in your face...

39:03.400 --> 39:06.700
and take your little black satchel
with all your hard-earned drug money, huh?

39:06.700 --> 39:10.900
- None of that ever happened, right?
- No police, no robbery.

39:12.200 --> 39:15.500
Okay. Just checkin'.

39:15.400 --> 39:18.600
Put down complainant uncooperative
and refused medical aid.

39:18.600 --> 39:20.500
You got it.

39:28.100 --> 39:30.900
We got a Ferdinand Hollie
shot on Second and Fifth.

39:30.900 --> 39:33.500
- Your office said to respond.
- Is he D.O. A?

39:33.400 --> 39:35.500
Looks like he's going out.
I'll lead you over.

40:02.600 --> 40:06.300
A guy got shot in the back, hurt bad.
Won't let anyone touch him.

40:08.200 --> 40:10.200
Ferdinand.

40:10.100 --> 40:13.100
Don't touch me, man.

40:13.900 --> 40:15.800
Just take it easy.

40:15.900 --> 40:17.800
It's hot.

40:20.200 --> 40:26.000
- Didn't mess up my work. I had those Colombians' case.
- All right.

40:25.800 --> 40:30.700
It was Marvin Freeland's crew
bushwhacked me after.

40:30.600 --> 40:32.500
Halfway down the block.

40:32.500 --> 40:36.300
- Who from Freeland's crew?
- Ask your homey in the hockey jacket.

40:38.300 --> 40:41.900
Eddie Leon capped me.
Didn't see the wheel man.

40:41.900 --> 40:45.500
Maybe you can check the E.R.'s.
I got two off.

40:45.400 --> 40:48.600
All right. We'll check
for any wounds with.44s.

40:51.300 --> 40:54.700
- I'm sorry, Ferdinand.
- Uh-uh.

40:54.700 --> 40:58.700
Said it was a favor, not rent.

40:58.600 --> 41:00.500
That left it up to me.

41:03.900 --> 41:07.600
Got no b-bodies
unaccounted for, Robert.

41:07.400 --> 41:12.000
D- D-Don't let 'em
clear no cases off me.

41:15.500 --> 41:17.700
Hey. Hey.

41:33.300 --> 41:35.600
We took this off him.

41:37.800 --> 41:40.000
Andy, you voucher this for me?

41:40.000 --> 41:43.000
I gotta go someplace.

41:46.100 --> 41:49.900
- I need a ride.
- Sure. Come on.

41:49.800 --> 41:53.200
Everybody use gloves.
Guy had the bug.

42:02.600 --> 42:05.800
No. I mean, this is true.

42:05.700 --> 42:08.800
Somebody down there
is wasting the alcohol. Forget it.

42:12.400 --> 42:14.400
We gotta talk.

42:14.300 --> 42:16.400
I've already had my Bible lesson.

42:19.000 --> 42:21.400
Let's... go.

42:26.500 --> 42:30.100
What? We going to the john? I needed
to do that for the last 20 minutes.

42:30.000 --> 42:32.000
- Come on.
- Yeah.

42:40.400 --> 42:43.800
Ferdinand Hollie got whacked
out on the street.

42:43.800 --> 42:47.800
Mm. What is the ceiling
for suspects? Fifty? Fifty-five?

42:47.700 --> 42:51.600
No, no, no. Marvin Freeland had him
capped, Kahlins, after you gave him up.

42:51.600 --> 42:54.400
Oh, God. You and me
have had this little chat.

42:54.400 --> 42:57.800
I have got no tears for your C.I.

42:57.700 --> 42:59.800
I will take a piss
in his honor, though...

42:59.700 --> 43:01.900
if you will vacate
the line of fire.

43:07.300 --> 43:10.100
He was a better guy
than you ever thought about being!

43:10.100 --> 43:12.000
And I am on a job with you!

43:12.000 --> 43:14.700
- We'll see for how long.
- Well, you go ahead.

43:14.600 --> 43:17.600
You bring up charges, Kahlins.
You go ahead. You get your witnesses.

43:17.600 --> 43:21.200
I bet there's a whole line of guys outside
waiting to stand up for you.

43:21.100 --> 43:25.400
Oh, God.

43:33.800 --> 43:36.100
Sorry for clearing out the place.

